# Core Rules

## Read Order
Before planning or editing, read:
1. `README.md`
2. `AGENTS.md`
3. `docs/00-index.md`
4. `docs/docs-policy.md`
5. relevant docs under `docs/`
6. relevant code/config/tests

## Source Of Truth
- Project facts live in `docs/`
- Execution rules live in `AGENTS.md` and this rules folder
- Do not infer intent from code alone when documentation exists

## Project Guardrails
- Keep the public API limited to `/ai/intake` and `/ai/report` unless requirements explicitly change
- Do not write secrets into `wrangler.jsonc`
- If `wrangler` bindings change, run `npx wrangler types`

## Default Behavior
- Prefer updating existing docs over creating new docs
- Keep changes scoped
- When requirements are fuzzy, refine docs first
- If a new doc is created, update `docs/00-index.md`
- Default to Simplified Chinese when writing plans or implementation breakdowns unless the task explicitly requires another language
- After each logically complete, testable round of code changes, you may run `npm run deploy` without re-asking
- This deploy permission applies after a finished change batch, not after every file save

## Required Final Output
At task end, report:
- code changes
- docs changes
- whether a new doc was created
- tests added or updated
- commands executed
- remaining risks
